Introduction :


	Small video "capture program" ideal for webcam testing and problem debugging.

	reference to http://www.quickcamteam.net/software/linux/v4l2-software/luvcview/

1.setting up your kernel configuration with this options to support UVC type USB video webcam


	    *check the list on both website .To know what type cam you are using now....

        UVC:http://www.ideasonboard.org/uvc/
        GSPCA:http://www.mjmwired.net/kernel/Documentation/video4linux/gspca.txt

        Device Drivers  --->
                Multimedia devices  --->
                         [*] Video capture adapters  --->
                                 [*]   V4L USB devices  --->
                                        <*>   USB Video Class (UVC)
                                        [*]     UVC input events device support
                                        <*>   GSPCA based webcams  --->
                                                <*>   SONIX JPEG USB Camera Driver

                         <*> Video For Linux

2. Download luvcview_port.tar.bz2 and decompress from /day5/ 
	(*this version has been modified and ifferent from original version)

3. plug in UVC webcam to Tiny4412 ,make Makefile,upload to Tiny4412 
 

	$make -j8
	$cp luvcview ~/root_mkfs	


4. run luvcview with UVC webcam plugged into Tiny4412

	*before you run luvcview , chenc if the UVC camera has been installed and shows /dev/video15

		[root@Tiny4412 /]# ls /dev/video*
		/dev/video0   /dev/video12  /dev/video2   /dev/video6
		/dev/video1   /dev/video13  /dev/video3   /dev/video7
		/dev/video10  /dev/video14  /dev/video4   /dev/video8
		/dev/video11  /dev/video15  /dev/video5   /dev/video9



	*you can check the parameter what luvcview has
		[root@Tiny4412 /]# ./luvcview -h
		luvcview version v0.2.4 
		usage: uvcview [-h -d -g -f -s -i -c -o -C -S -L -l -r] 
		-h      print this message 
		-d      /dev/videoX       use videoX device
		-g      use read method for grab instead mmap 
		-w      disable SDL hardware accel. 
		-f      video format  default jpg  others options are yuv jpg 
		-i      fps           use specified frame interval 
		-s      widthxheight      use specified input size 
		-c      enable raw frame capturing for the first frame
		-C      enable raw frame stream capturing from the start
		-S      enable raw stream capturing from the start
		-o      avifile  create avifile, default video.avi
		-L      query valid video formats
		-l      query valid controls and settings
		-r      read and set control settings from luvcview.cfg
		-O      get picture.


5. check the image format Camera support.

		[root@Tiny4412 /]# ./luvcview -d /dev/video15 -L
		luvcview version v0.2.4 
		video /dev/video15 
		/dev/video15 does not support read i/o
		{ pixelformat = 'YUYV', description = 'YUV 4:2:2 (YUYV)' }
